info.name: NIPR API Samples
info.description:
To facilitate the implementation of our services, NIPR has created a collection of sample requests for accessing APIs. This collection is designed for researching, testing, and troubleshooting service calls with NIPR APIs.

When troubleshooting, using this collection can help identify whether the issue lies with the client code or an unexpected response from the service.

If you have any questions about these services, please reach out to your NIPR Account Coordinator. To ensure we can assist you effectively, kindly include the services you’re accessing along with the XML request and response.

Follow these steps to start making NIPR webservice calls with Postman:

1. Import the Environment Parameter files from [https://wiki.nipr.com.](https://wiki.nipr.com.)
    
2. Set environment parameter values.

request.description:
Adds a Subscription and associated elements to an Alerts account.

A subscription defines the Affiliations, States and Categories for which you would like to receive updates.

1. Populate the subscriptionName element with a unique name for your new subscription
    
2. Populate the email element with who to contact for questions about this subscription
    
3. Populate the affiliationList element and sub-elements with affiliation information
    
4. Populate the stateList element with either All states or a specific list of states to target
    
5. Populate the alertTypeList with the desired categories to target
    
6. Send the request to create the new subscription.  
    An HTTP 200 response indicates the subscription was successfully added.

1. Populate both subscriptionName elements with the name for your subscription.  
    **Note:** Subscriptions cannot be renamed.

6. Send the request to update the settings for the subscription.  
    An HTTP 200 response indicates the subscription was successfully updated.

item.description:
PDB Alerts is a maintenance service designed to help companies keep data in sync with NIPR’s Entity Database (PDB). Detailed documentation for this service can be found at [NIPR's Industry Portal](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/NIPR+Industry+Portal): - PDB Alerts Web Service ([Getting Started](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Getting+Started+with+PDB+Alerts)) - [Business Version](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/PDB+Alerts+Web+Service+Business+Version) - [Schema](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/PDB+Alerts+Schema) - [Technical Version](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/PDB+Alerts+Web+Service+Technical+Version) This is a paid service. To access the PDB Alerts via web service, your **company administrator** must: - Issue an ID for your account in each environment to use for PDB Alerts - Contact your NIPR Account Coordinator to flag the IDs as a "Web Service" account and assign the PDB Alerts role - Assign the PDB Alerts product to your IDs in each environment - Log in to the PDB Alerts application in each environment and select a delivery method of either “Web Service” or “Composite” Once your account has been set up for accessing PDB Alerts, you can use the APIs in this collection to - Add new subscriptions - Review existing subscriptions - Edit existing subscriptions - Remove subscriptions - Add Targets to a subscription - Review existing targets for a subscription - Remove specific targets from a subscription - Remove all targets from a subscription - Retrieve alerts reports using the below methods: | **Report Method** | **Description** | | --- | --- | | Receive Specific Alerts Report
**(Recommended)** | Returns a PDB Alerts report containing all targets with changes for the given date for all subscriptions. | | Receive Specific Alerts Report For Subscription

item.description:
Receive a current list of Designated Responsible Licensed Entitys (DRLPs) associated with a firm.

type="LU" task="drlpList"

Determine an applicant's eligibility and fee estimate for a licensing application, contact change, or license update request.

Detailed documentation for these services can be found at [NIPR's Industry Portal](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/NIPR+Industry+Portal): [Eligibility Web Service](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Eligibility+Web+Service)

These are free services.

**Refer to the** [State Business Rules](https://pdb.nipr.com/Gateway/ViewBusRules) **for specific required data for each State and each product.**

**RL** = Resident Licensing

**RLR** = Resident License Renewals

**NRL** = Non-Resident Licensing

**NRR** = Non-Resident License Renewals

**ADHSRL** = Non-Resident Adjuster License with Designated Home State

**ADHSRR** = Non-Resident Adjuster License Renewal with Designated Home State

**NRLNHS** = Non-Resident License with No Home State

**NRRNHS** = Non-Resident Renewal with No Home State

**NRALNHS** = Non-Resident Adjuster License with No Home State

**NRARNHS** = Non-Resident Adjuster Renewal with No Home State

**ACR** = Address Change Request

**CCR** = Contact Change Request

**LU** = License Update

item.description:
Programmatically interface with NIPR Gateway to submit transactions for business rule processing and transmission to states.

Detailed documentation for this service can be found at [NIPR's Industry Portal](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/NIPR+Industry+Portal): [Real Time](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Gateway+Services)

This is a paid service.  
NIPR Transaction fees are collected via weekly invoice.  
State fees are collected nightly via EFT.

1. Prior to submitting license requests, use the Licensing Portal to determine the applicant's eligibility information and avoid unnecessary transaction rejections (not applicable to appointments and terminations).
    
2. Use the [Transaction XML Layout](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Gateway+Transaction+XML+Layout), [State Business Rules](https://pdb.nipr.com/Gateway/ViewBusRules), and [State Non-Uniform Questions (NUQs)](https://wiki.nipr.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=NTD&title=Non-Uniform+Questions) to build transaction XML according to state specific requirements. Refer to [State Requirements ](https://nipr.com/licensing-center/state-requirements) for helpful information for each state.
    
3. Submit Transaction XML to Real Time in batches of 100 or less to acheive the best performance.
    
    1. States that provide a _real time response_ are those States that are set up to process through our Centralized Processing method, do not use the NIPR State Interface for transactions (other than pended), and do not require the accepted transactions be sent to the State for prior approval.
        
    2. If NIPR cannot get a final response in real time, an _intermediate response_ will be generated for all transactions of all types.
        
    3. The URL ending with ‘realtime’ will return to the client responses from transactions sent **plus** responses from previously sent transactions that have received an additional intermediate response or final response since the original transmission. The URLs ending with ‘niprgw’ will return to the client only responses from transactions sent.
        
4. Submit requests to Real Time to receive updates for pended transactions.
    
    1. By default, multiple requests for the same transaction XML will result in a duplicate error. To receive transaction updates instead of a duplicate error response, contact your NIPR Account Coordinator to enable **polling** on your Gateway account.

item.description:
Used by states and industry to retrieve ecommerce / EFT information for transactions processed through the NIPR Gateway on a given date.

It is the responsibility of the client to develop and maintain the programs that use the Gateway Ecommerce Ledger Web Service (GEL-WS) to retrieve Gateway Ecommerce Reports.

Detailed documentation for this service can be found at [NIPR's Industry Portal](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/NIPR+Industry+Portal): [Ledger Web Service](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NIPRPORTAL/Ledger+Web+Service)

This is a free service.

Gateway Services allow you to send transaction information to NIPR for state validation. NIPR Gateway will pass valid transactions to the state's back office for processing. Detailed documentation for these services can be found at [NIPR's Industry Portal](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/NIPR+Industry+Portal): - Submitting Gateway Transactions ([Getting started](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Getting+Started+With+Gateway+Services)) - [Eligibility Web Service](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Eligibility+Web+Service) **(Is the applicant eligible to apply)** - [Glossary](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Glossary) - [Ledger Web Service](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NIPRPORTAL/Ledger+Web+Service) **(Gateway Ecommerce Ledger)** - [Non-Uniform Questions 08-09-2024.xlsx](https://wiki.nipr.com/download/attachments/1343496/Non-Uniform%20Questions%2008-09-2024.xlsx?version=1&modificationDate=1723214495601&api=v2) **Non-Uniform Questions (State specific questions outside the uniform application)** - [Real Time](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Gateway+Services) **(Application used to submit/retrieve your gateway transactions)** - [Error Codes](https://pdb.nipr.com/Gateway/ValidErrors) - [State Business Rules](https://pdb.nipr.com/Gateway/ViewBusRules) **(What information do I submit in my transaction)** - [Transaction Layout](https://wiki.nipr.com/display/NTD/Gateway+Transaction+XML+Layout) **(XML standards for all gateway transactions)** - [BQSD Uniform questions.xlsx](https://wiki.nipr.com/download/attachments/1343496/BQSD%20Universal%20questions.xlsx?version=1&modificationDate=1676041609478&api=v2) **(Background Supporting Document/ Uniform Background Questions) -must download to access** - [Transaction types.PNG](https://wiki.nipr.com/download/attachments/1343496/Transaction%20types.PNG?version=3&modificationDate=1695750389974&api=v2) **(Transaction type acronyms and descriptions)**
